        <content type="html" xml:base="https://blog.jimmac.eu/posts/evenmopixels/">&lt;p&gt;To keep the habbit alive, I continue to do a &lt;a href=&quot;&#x2F;posts&#x2F;mopixels&#x2F;&quot;&gt;daily pixel routine&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;, now covering almost all of the &lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;circle.gnome.org&quot;&gt;GNOME Circle&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; apps.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good call. Empty alt attributes (alt=&amp;quot;&amp;quot;) are actually better for decorative images or icons since they tell screen readers to skip over them, rather than announcing &amp;quot;x&amp;quot; over and over again.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
